DISCOVER MORE

DISCOVER BANFF

The Town of Banff is the ideal place to jump-start your Rocky Mountain adventure. You'll find a unique mix of urban amenities, access to endless winter activity and some of the best downhill skiing in the North American Rockies.  Think champagne powder, après cocktails, and a culinary haven set in a picturesque mountain town. Your must see?  The crown jewel of the Rockies, theiconic Fairmont Banff Springs.

EXPLORE YOUR STAY

DISCOVER JASPER

Winter in Jasper is a wonderland of snow sports. Ski or snowboard at Marmot Basin, try snowshoeing or cross-country skiing, explore the frozen waterfalls, ice caves, and incredible ice formations of Maligne Canyon, or skate on Lake Mildred. End your active day relaxing by a roaring fire or with a rejuvenating treatment at The Spa at The Fairmont Jasper Park Lodge.

EXPLORE YOUR STAY

DISCOVER LAKE LOUISE

Lake Louise offers an incredible variety of winter activities and events including the international ice carving festival - Ice Magic. A stunning alpine lake in summer, Lake Louise transforms into the world’s most spectacular outdoor ice rink, complete with an ice castle to glide through. Snow shoeing, dogsledding and skiing are right at the Fairmont Chateau Lake Louise’s door step or a short shuttle ride away.

EXPLORE YOUR STAY

DISCOVER EDMONTON

When the temperature drops in Edmonton, the real fun begins. From the spectacular Silver Skate Festival ice castle to the ice sculptures of Ice on Whyte, Edmonton is a true winter city.  It’s rich in adventure, culture, winter celebration, and even Northern Lights!  Stay at the Fairmont Hotel Macdonald, a luxury heritage railway hotel, conveniently situated in the heart of vibrant downtown.

EXPLORE YOUR STAY

DISCOVER CALGARY

Starting your Rocky Mountain adventure in Banff? Then fly into Cowtown. Calgary’s vibrant foodie scene has seen an explosion of independently-owned restaurants driven by innovative and often ground-breaking chefs, and the Fairmont Palliser is no exception. Set in the heart of the city, this historic hotel delivers a variety of handcrafted cocktails, afternoon tea and sumptuous breakfasts..

EXPLORE YOUR STAY

TRUE

Winter is Coming to the Canadian Rockies, are you?

Book your Canadian Rockies winter adventure, where you’ll experience the ultimate winter playgrounds: Banff, Lake Louise, and Jasper, Alberta. Start your adventure by flying into Edmonton or Calgary, two of Canada’s most dynamic winter cities and gateways to the Canadian Rockies. Here you’ll experience the arts, winter festivals, authentic local dining & endless activities.

Travel through two of Canada's largest National Parks, home to unspoiled wilderness and one of the world’s most scenic drives, the Icefields Parkway. From hitting the slopes at one of our world-class ski resorts to dogsledding the Continental Divide; or viewing the Aurora Borealis from the dark skies of Jasper to celebrating Ice Magic in Lake Louise, our True North Rockies delivers an unparalleled winter escape.

The Canadian Rockies Will Take Your Breath Away

Rugged Landscapes and Authentic Adventures

Banff & Lake Louise is one of those places that truly leaves a lasting impression. The world’s third oldest national park, people have been drawn to these mountains and lakes for a long time - and when you visit you’ll understand why.

True Escape

3,000 Vertical Feet of Superb Skiing & Snowboarding

Ski & Snowboard in Jasper

Escape the crowded resorts in favor of Marmot Basin, where lift lines are virtually non-existent, powder stashes last and the wide open slopes are yours to enjoy! Located in the breathtaking, mountainous landscape of Jasper National Park, Marmot Basin is a truly unique skiing destination, with a wide variety of runs on four mountain faces and over 3000 vertical feet of terrain to explore.

TRUE GRANDEUR

Heritage and Charm in the City

Fairmont Palliser,
Calgary’s Premier Address in the Centre of the City

Set in the heart of downtown Calgary, Fairmont Palliser is defining the iconic Calgary experience. Calgary’s friendly spirit, coupled with the city’s vibrant urban ambience makes for a metropolis of wonderful contrasts. Fairmont Palliser is a historical landmark offering distinctive accommodation in elegant surroundings.


Learn More

Fairmont MacDonald,
Edmonton’s Chateau on the River

Edmonton’s landmark, 4 diamond luxury hotel, Fairmont Hotel Macdonald, has been the setting of the city’s finest events and an iconic fixture of Edmonton’s skyline since July 5th, 1915. Situated in the heart of downtown and standing high on the bank overlooking the largest urban parkway in North America, the North Saskatchewan River Valley, Fairmont Hotel Macdonald's charm and classic elegance have made us Edmonton's place for every occasion.

True Wonder

Power Down & Look Up!

Jasper Dark Sky Preserve

Jasper is a mecca for stargazing adventurers. Get lost in the wonder of the second largest dark sky preserve in the world - an area where almost no artificial lighting is visible at night.

There’s No Hibernating Here

Welcome to Edmonton. We throw axes for fun, barbecue in blizzards and snowshoe with bison. From acre-sized castles made of ice to North America’s largest shopping mall that spans over 48 city blocks, we’ve never been afraid to do things a little differently.

Calgary, Where Canada Happens

Winter in Calgary is a magical time. Snow-covered streets, outdoor skating, twinkling lights combine to set the ultimate winter cityscape. From catching the energy of an NHL game with thousands of your new best friends or engaging in snow sports, to enjoying diverse nightlife with enthusiastic locals or sampling the incredible dining scene, Calgary is where Canada happens.     #WELOVEWINTER CONTEST DETAILS

    Are you a social media buff who loves winter? We want you to join us as our “Guest-agrammer!” Share your favorite winter moment with us for a chance to win a trip of a lifetime through two of Canada’s largest National Parks. You’ll join us on a seven day adventure in Banff, Lake Louise and Jasper, Alberta where you’ll experience all our winter wonderland has to offer. Ski the Canadian Rockies. Dog sled over the Great Divide. Snowshoe in the moonlight. Stargaze in some of the darkest skies in the world. Then share it with the world.
